     Programs

   Because environmental issues are often broad in scope, Cal/EPA
   coordinates a variety of programs that involve more than one of the
   agencies that it oversees. These programs are listed below. Be sure to
   visit the sites of Cal/EPA's constituent agencies (see links on our
   home page, as well as below) to to learn more about the broad variety
   of programs that they conduct individually.
     * Cross-Media Programs
     * Air Quality Programs
     * Toxic/Hazardous Materials and Substances Programs
     * Water Quality Programs
     * Waste Management Programs
     * Permit-Related Programs
     * Enforcement/Inspection-Related Programs

   Cross-Media Programs
   These programs address issues that involve air, water, waste and other
   environmental and health concerns.
     * California-Baja California Border Environmental Program
     * Environmental Justice Program
     * Environmental Management and Sustainability Project
     * Environmental Protection Indicators for California (EPIC)
     * Environmental Task Force
     * Environmental Technology Certification Program
     * Multimedia Chrome Plating Inspection Project
     * Site Designation Committee

   Air Quality Programs
   See the Air Resources Board site to learn about more programs in this
   area.

   Toxic/Hazardous Materials and Substances Programs
   See the Department of Toxic Substances Control site to learn about more
   programs in this area.
     * Clean Brownfields Loan Program
     * Proposition 65
     * Registered Environmental Assessor Program
     * Underground Storage Tank Program

   Waste Management Programs
   See the Integrated Waste Management Board site to learn about more
   programs in this area.

   Water Quality Programs
   See the State Water Resources Control Board site to learn about more
   programs in this area.
     * Proposition 65
     * Underground Storage Tank Program

   Permit-Related Programs
     * Cal GOLD: Business Permit Information
     * Unified Program
     * Permit Assistance Centers
     * Permit Consolidation Pilot Program

   Enforcement/Inspection-Related Programs
     * Enforcement Order Search for Cal/EPA Boards, Departments, and
       Offices
     * Unified Program
     * Environmental Task Force
     * Inspector Certification
     * Local Solid Waste Enforcement Agencies (LEA)
     * Multimedia Chrome Plating Inspection Project
     * Registered Environmental Assessor (REA) Program
     * Site Designation Committee

   Last updated: January 08, 2002
